pageContext.claim: “I listen to the Democrats, let me nice, just say the Democrats, I won't be specific, and they say, "Oh, everything comes through the port." They don't do that. They drive out where there's no barrier, no wall, they make a left.”
pageContext.analysis: It's not just Democrats. Trump's own Drug Enforcement Administration says most of the drugs cross the southern border through legal points of entry, while the United Nations says most human trafficking also goes through legal ports of entry.
